DIV1.P:
That, at half past two o'clock in the afternoon of this day, the boat of the ship Regulus, at anchor this morning in this road, came on board of his vessel, commanded by an officer of the said ship, and took out of the said vessel the following men;


David Murcie, master;

Thomas Dick, negro man;

William Bennet, negro man;

Thomas Danny, negro man.
